      "content": "that's exactly what i'm looking for. it's a really powerful way to frame it. \n\none thing though, i don't want my professor to think i'm just being one-sided. in the conclusion, how should i handle the \"other side\"? like, should i even give a real platform to the people who believe in individual responsibility and the importance of property rights, or would that just weaken my main argument about systemic change?",
